Description:
    Generates a custom ModelSettings module with full structure including
    implementation file, tests, and documentation.

Example:
    rails generate model_settings:module AuditTrail

    This will create:
        lib/model_settings/modules/audit_trail.rb
        spec/model_settings/modules/audit_trail_spec.rb
        docs/modules/audit_trail.md

Options:
    --skip-tests
        Skip generating test file

    --skip-docs
        Skip generating documentation file

    --exclusive-group=NAME
        Register module in an exclusive group (e.g., 'authorization')
        Only one module from the same exclusive group can be active at a time

    --options=OPTION:TYPE [OPTION2:TYPE2 ...]
        Register custom DSL options with validators
        Available types: symbol, boolean, string, array, hash

Examples:
    # Basic module
    rails generate model_settings:module AuditTrail

    # Module in exclusive group
    rails generate model_settings:module CustomAuth --exclusive-group=authorization

    # Module with custom options
    rails generate model_settings:module Workflow --options=state:symbol notify:boolean

    # Skip tests and documentation
    rails generate model_settings:module SimpleModule --skip-tests --skip-docs

After generation:
    1. Edit lib/model_settings/modules/your_module.rb
    2. Implement your module logic (search for TODO comments)
    3. Run tests: bundle exec rspec spec/model_settings/modules/your_module_spec.rb
    4. Update documentation in docs/modules/your_module.md

For detailed information, see:
    docs/architecture/module_development_api.md
